OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA wet start today, with the
OL,6,Frain heavy in places and accompanied
OL,7,Fby gusty winds. The rain will clear to
OL,8,Fthe east by lunchtime leading to a
OL,9,Fmuch drier and brighter afternoon with
OL,10,Fsunny spells. Feeling rather cool for
OL,11,FJune.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FLargely dry this evening
OL,14,Facross the east but scattered showers
OL,15,Ffurther west will tend to spread a
OL,16,Flittle further east overnight. A
OL,17,Frather chilly night for June.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
